#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:1
msgid "Adaptive Speculative Decoding"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:3
msgid ""
"Adaptive speculative decoding lets SGLang adjust `speculative_num_steps/"
"speculative_num_draft_tokens` at runtime instead of keeping a single fixed "
"value for the whole server lifetime. It is designed for workloads whose "
"accept length changes over time, where one static step count is rarely "
"optimal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:6
msgid "Current support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:8
msgid "Only `--speculative-algorithm EAGLE`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:9
msgid "Only `--speculative-eagle-topk 1`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:10
msgid ""
"If either condition is not met, SGLang falls back to static speculative "
"settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:12
msgid "Why adaptive steps help"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:14
msgid ""
"`speculative_num_steps` controls how many draft-model autoregressive steps "
"run in each speculative round. In practice, the best value depends on the "
"current workload."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:16
msgid ""
"If `num_steps` is too small, the draft model could have produced more "
"accepted tokens, but the round stops too early."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:17
msgid ""
"If `num_steps` is too large, the draft model produces many candidate tokens "
"that the target model rejects, so extra draft work is wasted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:19
msgid ""
"Real traffic often moves between high-acceptance and low-acceptance phases, "
"so one fixed step count is usually a compromise. Adaptive mode tries to "
"follow the workload instead of hard-coding a single global `num_steps`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:21
msgid "Design overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:23
msgid "The adaptive mechanism has three pieces:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:25
msgid "`AdaptiveSpeculativeParams`: the EMA-based policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:26
msgid "`SpecRuntimeState`: the per-tier runtime state bundle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:27
msgid ""
"`AdaptiveController`: the coordinator that chooses a tier and activates the "
"matching runtime state"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:29
msgid ""
"At startup, SGLang pre-builds one runtime state per candidate tier. By "
"default, the candidate tiers are `candidate_steps = [1, 3, 7]`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:31
msgid ""
"┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n"
"│                      SpecRuntimeState                    │\n"
"│                                                          │\n"
"│  speculative_num_steps / speculative_num_draft_tokens   │\n"
"│                                                          │\n"
"│  ┌────────────────┐ ┌────────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐  │\n"
"│  │  Draft stage   │ │  Verify stage  │ │ Extend stage │  │\n"
"│  │                │ │                │ │              │  │\n"
"│  │  attn_backend  │ │  attn_backend  │ │ attn_backend │  │\n"
"│  │  cuda_graph    │ │  cuda_graph    │ │ cuda_graph   │  │\n"
"│  └────────────────┘ └────────────────┘ └──────────────┘  │\n"
"└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:46
msgid ""
"This matters because `CudaGraphRunner` is shape-dependent. Each candidate "
"tier owns its own graph and backend state, so runtime switching is a "
"reference swap, not an online graph recapture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:48
msgid "Runtime flow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:50
msgid ""
"The adaptive update happens after verify and affects the next round, not the "
"current one:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:52
msgid ""
"┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n"
"│           EAGLEWorker.forward_batch_generation() — decode path      │\n"
"│                                                                     │\n"
"│   ① draft(batch)                                                    │\n"
"│       │  draft model multi-step generation with current tier        │\n"
"│       v                                                             │\n"
"│   ② verify(batch, spec_info)                                        │\n"
"│       │  target model tree verification                             │\n"
"│       │  → produces accept_length_per_req                           │\n"
"│       v                                                             │\n"
"│   ③ forward_draft_extend_after_decode(batch)                        │\n"
"│       │  draft model KV-cache catch-up                              │\n"
"│       v                                                             │\n"
"│   ④ adaptive_controller.on_verify_complete(accept_lengths)          │\n"
"│       │                                                             │\n"
"│       │  update EMA, apply warmup / interval / hysteresis gates     │\n"
"│       │  if tier changed, select a pre-built state from pool        │\n"
"│       v                                                             │\n"
"│     worker.apply_runtime_state(state)                               │\n"
"│                                                                     │\n"
"│   Tier switch happens after the current round completes.            │\n"
"│   Backends and CUDA graphs are never swapped mid-round.             │\n"
"└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:78
msgid "How the policy decides"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:80
msgid ""
"After each verify pass, SGLang reads the accepted draft length per request, "
"computes the batch average, smooths it with an exponential moving average "
"(EMA), and switches among the pre-built candidate tiers `[1, 3, 7]` by "
"default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:82
msgid "The decision logic is intentionally conservative:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:84
msgid "`warmup_batches` skips the first few batches"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:85
msgid "`update_interval` avoids switching every batch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:86
msgid "`down_hysteresis` and `up_hysteresis` reduce oscillation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:88
msgid ""
"Conceptually, the policy probes one step beyond the observed acceptance:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:90
msgid ""
"target_steps ≈ clamp(round(ema_accept_len) + 1, min(candidate_steps), "
"max(candidate_steps))\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:94
msgid ""
"So if recent requests consistently accept more drafted tokens, the policy "
"tends to move up. If they start rejecting earlier, it tends to move down."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:96
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:98
msgid ""
"`--speculative-adaptive-config` is optional, but the speculative setup still "
"needs to be valid for adaptive mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:100
msgid ""
"python3 -m sglang.launch_server \\\n"
"    --model meta-llama/Llama-2-7b-chat-hf \\\n"
"    --speculative-algorithm EAGLE \\\n"
"    --speculative-draft-model-path lmsys/sglang-EAGLE-llama2-chat-7B \\\n"
"    --speculative-eagle-topk 1 \\\n"
"    --speculative-num-steps 3 \\\n"
"    --speculative-num-draft-tokens 4 \\\n"
"    --speculative-adaptive\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:111
msgid ""
"If you want to override the defaults, add `--speculative-adaptive-config /"
"path/to/adaptive_spec.json`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:113
msgid "Example config:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:115
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"candidate_steps\": [1, 3, 7],\n"
"  \"ema_alpha\": 0.2,\n"
"  \"warmup_batches\": 10,\n"
"  \"update_interval\": 5\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:124
msgid "Config file reference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/adaptive_speculative_decoding.md:126
msgid "The config file is optional. Any omitted keys use defaults."
msgstr ""

